d_at": "2022-08-26T17:30:18Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut bytes = vec![0u8; 128 as usize];\r\n    println!(\"bytes: {:?}, len: {}\", bytes, bytes.len());\r\n\r\n    let id = 1234u32;\r\n    let hello = \"Hello, world!\".to_string();\r\n    let port_number = 8080u16;\r\n    let some_random_string = \"Some random string\".to_string();\r\n\r\n    bytes.splice(0..4, id.to_be_bytes());\r\n    bytes.splice(5..25, hello.as_bytes().to_vec());\r\n    bytes.splice(25..27, port_number.to_be_bytes());\r\n    bytes.splice(27..47, some_random_string.as_bytes().to_vec());\r\n\r\n    println!(\"bytes: {:?}, len: {}\", bytes, bytes.len());\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you see, I allocated 128 bytes of u8. The first print instruction shows the bytes and the size of the vector correctly (128). However, after adding data with `splice`, the size of the vector changes to 119. \r\nIt seems that the last `splice` with `some_random_string` eliminates some bytes from the end.\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.62.1 (e092d0b6b 2022-07-16)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: e092d0b6b43f2de967af0887873151bb1c0b18d3\r\ncommit-date: 2022-07-16\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.62.1\r\nLLVM version: 14.0.5\r\n```\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "vahidmohsseni", "id": 16836618, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2ODM2NjE4", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16836618?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vahidmohsseni", "html_url": "https://github.com/vahidmohsseni", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vahidmohsseni/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vahidmohsseni/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vahidmohsseni/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vahidmohsseni/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users